-- Nomura Raises $70 Million Tapping Mideast Islamic Market for First Time
-- Shaji Mathew
-- 2010-07-15T07:30:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-15/nomura-raises-70-million-tapping-mideast-islamic-market-for-first-time.html

          
          
             Nomura Holdings Inc. raised $70
million through a commodity murabaha facility, becoming the
first Japanese company to enter the Islamic finance market in
the Middle East, according to a company statement today.  
 The original target was $50 million and ABC Islamic Bank
was the sole mandated lead arranger for the facility, it said.
The facility has a three-year tenor and offers a profit margin
of 175 basis points per annum, it said.  
 The other arrangers of the facility included Islamic
Development Bank, Samba Financial Group, Sumitomo Mitsui Banking
Corp. and Ahli United Bank, according to the statement.  
          
          


  


        